02/07/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A roundtable discussion on judicial reform and drafting the national strategy for the judicial sector took place in Skopje on Thursday (1 July). 
Prime Minister Hari Kostov opened the forum, in which legal experts, prosecutors, and judges participated. 
They agreed that the country needs a concise strategy, harmonised with the EU, for judicial reform and a concrete timetable for its implementation. 
The participants expressed concern that the current image of the judicial system is one of inefficiency and corruption. 
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 02/07/04; A1 TV - 01/07/04)
